<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-11T22:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-11T22:25:00-05:00" n="786" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2530</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VDH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Van
                                    Dyke</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-11T22:25:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1916, 10.25 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>311. Department informed that Netherlands Oversea Trust has within a
                                month authorized consigned to it following shipments coffee: 15,000
                                bags from Brazil, 10,000 from Venezuela, 5,000 from Africa, 20,000
                                from London, 10,000 from Havre, but that no permits issued for
                                shipments from United States except small shipments in transit from
                                Central America and for Dutch Army. Investigate and if this prove
                                true vigorously protest against this apparent discrimination.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>